Description:
UK Industry’s Chemical, Biological, Radiological and Nuclear Defence Special Interest Group.

The aim of CBRN-UK is to act as a focal point to represent the interests of its members to UK Government Departments, Overseas Governments and other organisations or companies concerned with the CBRN sector of business. CBRN-UK provides:
- a gateway to the UK CBRN industry;
- a focus for UK Government departments to turn to when seeking an industrial view when formulating policy in the CBRN field and a focal point for industry to represent its views to HMG;
- a co-ordinating function to communicate with overseas governments and organisations concerned with CBRN equipment or service area and which HMG can utilise to host incoming delegations;
- forums in which members and observers can discuss, in confidence, CBRN issues of mutual interest;
- opportunities for members to participate in shared marketing activities e.g. exhibitions, conferences; and
- opportunities for informed speakers to address members on current and appropriate issues concerned with the CBRN environment.

West Coast Solutions is a talented team of technical experts with the singular vision of optimally and synergistically serving the needs of the defense and advanced technology marketplaces. Delivering world class solutions requires achieving and maintaining a laser-like focus on all aspects of the customer’s needs, which necessarily spans all aspects of the supporting organization, not just engineering. West Coast Solutions understands this. 
 
Excellence is achieved by bringing all the right parties to the table, and most importantly, the varied perspectives they represent. Our founder’s career has included tours of duty within academia, a large business prime contractor, and several small businesses, providing our team with a uniquely broad insight into where the answers to the hard questions can best be found. 
 
The WCS Team brings proven expertise to:
identify and procure (through invention or acquisition) the necessary critical technologies;
build the right team for the job, drawing on our network of world-class talent;
construct a realistic program plan that optimally balances risk, cost and schedule;
execute all phases from concept design through prototype development and delivery.
 
WCS leverages our core competencies in power electronics, alternative energy, and cryogenics to the immediate benefit of our customers. The key is our focus on niche needs best met by a small, agile operation. By focusing on consulting, design and rapid prototyping, WCS is available to provide an immediate “value add” to larger organizations, effectively becoming an extension of your team in an overall business construct. In complement to these design services, WCS is developing niche products to provide yet another “value add” proposition for the customers we serve.

Please visit our full site at www.wecoso.com for a more complete company description.

Proino is a multidisciplinary Engineering Company which specializes in Defense industry. We mainly focus on developing high-tech and patent-worthy products while giving design, analysis, test and consultancy services.
Due to our management and technical background on various areas of expertise we can create a whole solution from the contract to the delivery.

Our mission is;
To design and develop genuine sub-systems for local and foreign System Integrators with up-to-date and future technology.

Our vision is;

To develop patent rewarding innovative products and being preferred sub-system supplier for local and foreign market.

Mission:

Authenticity, Leadership, & Technical Adaptability (ALTA); 

Our goal is to provide top-tier talent to support the intelligence community, industry and telecommunications applications.  Our team is composed of experienced trainers and subject matter experts with extensive knowledge of the latest technologies and best practices in defense. We are dedicated to helping our clients improve their mission support, skills and knowledge, and ultimately enhance their professional capabilities.

The Vidar Group is owned and operated by former and current Warfighters including special operators from our nation’s most prestigious units. We employ current and former Service Members (Conventional & SOF) that have spent their careers devising operational response methodologies for high risk and rapidly changing situations. Since 2017, Vidar has been developing and providing Student Aircrew training for NATO, US, and Commercial MQ-9 Reaper customers. We have revolutionized the way aircrews train, bringing the training 'off-range' to realistic training environments. Our team hails from conventional and special operations backgrounds and has vast, real-world experience in all SOF Mission sets, giving full spectrum expertise to our nation's student aircrews. 

Some of our fields of expertise:
- Program & Project Management; 
- Explosive Ordnance Disposal & Training;
- Small Unit Tactics (SUT) & Close Quarters Battle (CQB);
- Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) tactics, techniques, and procedures;
- Formal Courseware Development & Training; 
- Operational Planning, Design, Execution, and Analysis;
- Close Air Support (CAS) & Close Combat Attack (CCA);
- Rotary and Fixed Wing Aircraft Operations;
- Combat & Medicine;
- sUAS Mobile Training.

The rapidly changing market trends and environmental issues challenge the boundaries of traditional engineered alloys and manufacturing processes.  

Aiming to keep ahead of the technological trends while lowering costs and reducing emissions, Qmex Technology is created to innovate more high-performance alloys and mission-critical parts for space & aerospace, semicon, defense, power, maritime, petrochemical and other high-tech industrial markets. 

Our strength lies in developing innovative alloys and processes to increase its thermal-mechanical performances concerning reusability, pressure-retaining, wear, heat and corrosion-resistant, cryogenic and shock resistance, and cost & weight reduction. 

3 High-Tech Divisions
1.	Q-Metal Lab
•	Reusable high-strength alloys (Rocket, other space applications);
•	High temperature and corrosion-resistant stainless steels (burner systems);
•	Corrosion and abrasion-resistance steels for harsh environments;
•	Alloys with ultra-high-strength, shock and high impact resistance (excavations, armour);
•	Superalloys (Space, Aerospace applications);
•	Low thermal expansion coefficient alloys (semicon applications);
•	Shape memory alloys ( space, medical applications);
•	Metal matrix composite, with low thermal expansion coefficient but high thermal conductivity (semicon);
•	Additive manufacturing powder metallurgy for space and medical applications ; 
•      etc. 

2.	Manufacturing Technologies  
•	Investment casting / lost wax, almost all alloys possible
•      Additive manufacturing (3D Printing)
•	Metal injection molding
•	Die casting 

3.	Green components 
•	Green manufacturing Technology Innovations: reusable, sustainable, lower costs, shorten lead time and increase performance. Achieving emission reduction. 
•      Eco-Design components with optimal materials and process choice;  
•	High-performance key components, such as engine and structural parts.

Our dream is to build a community of passionate, inspired space fans, who feel that humanity’s future is in, and depends on, space.

We want to inspire people outside the space community to be passionate about, and engage in, the new developments in space, be it as space entrepreneurs, political leaders, researchers, activists or simply as informed citizens. Space already has a massive impact on our lives, and will continue to do so – but we need more people to be involved in such an important endeavour for humanity.

Powering Space is a constellation of space organisations, foundations and individuals, with three main ambitions:

- to diffuse space knowledge and awareness globally;
- to educate key stakeholders from the political, business and cultural realms, about the fundamentals of space; 
- and to facilitate communication and cooperation between those engaged in space outreach.

